Summary: Assembly completion error- HELP
Description:
Hello Ascii team,

Need your help urgently as this assembly completion error is gating our ability to ship parts to our data centers for upgrades.

Here's a summary of the process for Hawksbill....

The card 1025651-03 ships from Cavium (Supplier) to our Oakley Hub, It's then MOR'd to our NYC office (which is set up as a CM).
Our NY office provisions the cards and changes the PN to 1027739-03 and then does assembly completion and MOR units back to Oakley so the units can be shipped to the various DCs for upgrades.

We have been doing this for a couple of years now so not sure why we're having Assembly completion issues now. Can you please help ?
We need to resolve this issue asap so units can ship out of NYC office. This process has previously worked without any assembly completion issues on PN 1025651-01 and 1025651-02 and 1027739-01 and 1027739-02. We now have an issue with the  1025651-03 and 1027739-03 and need your help.

Agile BOM set up is correct. 
1025651-03 - Supply type is NPI consigned ; Oracle Template is Ops Purchased
1027739-03- Supply type is NPI consigned ; Oracle Template is Ops CM Make

PO issued was an OSP PO.

Here's the issue we're facing....
Our assembly-complete of 30 pcs of 1027739-03 failed with this error, " SCP00425ERROR: Onhand Quantity not sufficient for item 1025651-03 in Org ZOR. There are indeed 30 units of 1025651-03 under ZOR ( CMGONY1P) to cover this Assembly Completion. Please help fix the error that is causing this failure. 

Appreciate it.
Worklog:
Thanks for reaching out to ASCII Oracle Support team for help. This ticket has been triaged by Ticketron, a Google AI powered solution. For more information, please visit go/ticketron.Hi Helen

Would you be able to provide the OSP PO # for these AC transactions?

Thanks,
AdityaThe "blanket PO number" that appears in go/scportal is 5000088


NormYes, PO# 5000088. Thanks Aditya.Hi Helen/ Norm

I see the blanket PO # 5000088 in the SC Portal. However, I couldn't find the AC transaction in Oracle with respective GPNs.
Could you let me know if there were any AC transactions reported against the PO # 5000088 in SC Portal with the items? Also can you provide the screenshot where you have seen the error message?

Thanks,
AdityaHi Aditya,
I don't think it created a transaction before, it did not go that far.  It failed on the "validate" step.
Just now I tried it again (to get the screenshot) -- and it worked! SCP37354 has been created.
I guess the problem fixed itself, whatever it was.  

Thank you for your help.

NormThanks for the update, Norm.

Looks like it was a timing issue related to GPN. As the issue is now resolved, I am going ahead with marking this ticket as resolved. Please reopen or file a new ticket if you need any further assistance on this.

Thanks,
Aditya

Description:
Hi P2P Team,

The following PO 1010019416 failed to process in Lager as the Incoterms code present in the PO is "DAP-SHIPMENT". Our PINT system could not find mapping rules implemented for Incoterms code "DAP-SHIPMENT". Can you please check why DAP-SHIPMENT is used in PO instead of only using DAP.

Till now what all PO's we received for TOSHIBA MEMORY AMERICA always have Incoterms as "DAP-SHIPMENT".

Please check the screenshot present below. 

Let us know if a new mapping rule needs to be implemented on this Incoterm code or is this Invalid and wrongly sent.

Thanks,
Sachit Anand

This is a new incoterm created under Android business group.

Hi Sandeep,

Please confirm on the mapping rule to Sachit. 

Thanks,
Harika+ Clark,

Clark, we have introduced new Incoterms "CIP-SHIPMENT" and "DAP-SHIPMENT" in Prod similar to FCA-SHIPMENT (Existing). 

Currently if Oracle PO has FCA-SHIPMENT then Lager is sending FCA in EDI850 out to Supplier.

So for the new incoterms, We want send DAP -If oracle pass DAP-SHIPMENT and CIP if Oracle sends CIP-SHIPMENT.

Summary: Schedule Revisit- Inventory Transaction Manager and Cost Manager
Description:
Dear Support team,

It seems Inventory Transaction Manager is scheduled to run every 5 mins in Production.
We would like to know if it can be increased to run every 2 hours instead.

Please share if it would cause any adverse affect.

Thanks
Shaswat
Worklog:
Thanks for reaching out to ASCII Oracle Support team for help. This ticket has been triaged by Ticketron, a Google AI powered solution. For more information, please visit go/ticketron.Hi Indra,
Could you please help.

Thanks
Ram2 minutes, not 2 hours, are meant.

We want to understand why or how the timing of Inventory Transaction Manager is set to 5 minutes. (in EBSUAT, the timing was set to 2 minutes.)

What could be the minimum timing that will work for EBS Prod?Hi William

Currently the material transaction manager launch is scheduled for every 5 mins. The schedule was unchanged from when we took up  the ascii support. The schedule can be changed to 2 mins. Per Oracle, it can be scheduled in 2, 5 or 10 mins. When we have huge uncosted transactions, we usually flip the timing of Cost Manager from 2 to 1 minute.

2 minutes for inventory transaction manager should work in transaction processing in Oracle. If you need any more details, please let me know.

Thanks,
AdityaReference: b/126953987

Thanks
RamHi Aditya,

Could you please go ahead with changing the schedule to 2 min.
Also, could you please monitor the same for next few days to see that there are no unwanted issues.

Thanks
RamHow do we increase the priority of this request.

Thanks
RamHi Ram/Shaswat,

Process transaction interface is already scheduled to run every 2 minutes.

Thanks,
RiteshHi Ram

Sorry for the delay in response. Concurrent Request 'Process transaction interface has been scheduled to run every 2 minutes.
Please find the below screenshot for your reference.

https://screenshot.googleplex.com/K62FAy0e8Df.png

I will be monitoring the same for next few days to stay away from unwanted issues. 
As there is no pending action on IT team, I am going ahead with marking this ticket as resolved. Please reopen or file a new ticket if you need any further assistance on this. I'd be glad to help.

Thanks,
Aditya

As per my conversation with Tiana, I'm providing the details below regarding those PO's which having issue (Restriction in Oracle) of not sending PO ASN (EDI) out to CM.

PO#520217
Supplier : GLOBALFOUNDRIES US INC
Supplier Site :  NEW YORK USD1  [Site ID : 1652835]

PO# 1010009757
Supplier : GOLD CIRCUIT ELECTRONICS CO LTD
Supplier Site :  CHUNGLI  [Site ID : 176497]

PO#1010008981
Supplier : TTM TECHNOLOGIES TRADING ASIA COMPANY LIMITED
Supplier Site :  HONG KONG USD  [Site ID : 1555905]

Below query retrieves supplier site IDs from the table which is stopping the PO ASN [EDI] sending out to CM.
SELECT * 
FROM xxmfg.xxmfg_asn_sf_wolf_loc_codes 
WHERE supplier_site_id in (1652835,176497, 1555905);

Please remove these supplier site IDS (above) from the table to resolve this ticket similar to the solution provided in some old ticket [t/30711035+Satya

Hi Santosh,

removing these sites from xxmfg_asn_sf_wolf_loc_codes means marking these supplier sites as non integrated. Any new PO created for these suppliers sites will also send PO ASN to 3PL post change but if supplier is reporting ASN via scportal/E2open, it will not be sent to 3PL.
So please confirm you want to make these changes.


Thanks,
Vikrant Hi Vikranth,

I just spoke to Satya as well. He has agreed that the scope of this ticket should

1. Disable these supplier sites (set active_flag = N) in the table xxmfg_asn_sf_wolf_loc_codes.
2. Generate PO ASN (EDI for total quantity) to CM for only these 3 PO's  (520217, 1010009757, 1010008981)
3. Enable these supplier sites (set active_flag = Y) back in the table.     (Otherwise In case if not enabled,  it would impact other PO's using the same supplier site)

Please go-ahead and confirm.

Regards,
Santosh.Thanks Santosh. Let me work on this.Thanks Santosh & VikrantHi Tiana,

This is completed and ASNs have been sent to Inventec with ICNs 200006801,200006800 and 200006799

Please check with CM if they can receive the PO now and let me know if this ticket can be closed.Tiana,

Can we close this?Closing this ticket as no further action pending on support.

Summary: Incorrect data structure in EDI 856
Description:
Hi Oracle team,

We have received below email from partner Syncreon today.
---------------------------------------------
Pandora, could you review this 856 please

I believe your 856 structure is bad here (HL).  We expect S/O/P/I

This has S/I/O

ISA*00*          *00*          *01*00060902413PRD *ZZ*SYNCREONB2BEDIP*190402*0745*U*00401*200735318*0*P*|~GS*SH*0060902413B2B*SYNFAIRBURN*20190402*0745*1141017*X*004010~ST*856*1141017~BSN*00*36363772*20190402*0000**PZ~HL*1**S~REF*8X*ASN~DTM*002*20190402*0000~DTM*017*20190402*0000~N1*ST*SYNCREON*91*WHGAFB1P~N3*Google LLC c/o Syncreon,1000 Logistics Center Dr.,Ste.*200~N4*Fairburn**30213*US*SP*GA~N1*SF*INNOLIGHT TECHNOLOGY SUZHOU LTD*91*VENDOR-ASN~N3*3 RESULT WAY~N4*CUPERTINO**95014*US*SP*CA~HL*1*2*I~LIN*1*VP*1037522***CH*CN~SN1**220*EA**220*EA~REF*JB*NPI0416~HL*2*1*O~PRF*1010017751~CTT*1~SE*20*1141017~GE*1*1141017~IEA*1*200735318~
---------------------------------------------

The structure reported in the ASN is incorrect, it should be shipment - order - item but it has been mentioned as shipment- item - order in the OUTBOUND ASN sent to Syncreon.

When I checked for the corresponding inbound ASN file, we are receiving it from "INNOLIGHT TECHNOLOGY SUZHOU LTD" through e2open and it is non-EDI also there are no structure details mentioned in the inbound ASN.

This is the same case for all the inbound ASN's which we are receiving through e2open and the corresponding ASN_Of also having the structure  shipment- item - order which is incorrect, but so far only syncreon reported this issue and we didn't here from any other partner yet.

Could you please look into this issue or route this ticket to correct team? we also have bug b/129749697 if in case you would like to route to respective team / person.

Thanks,
Varalakshmi

Thanks!Hi Sunil

Please find the below observations.

I could see that shipments were cancelled against PO # 1010015647 with cancel reason 'EDI Signal Cancel'. However, the quantity wasn't received against any of these shipments. Earlier we had a bug # 71770762 where the shipments got cancelled after the creation of receipts. To overcome this, Oracle suggested a datafix to restore a cancelled PO shipment. As the quantity was not received now, the PO shipment can be deleted and entered in the application.

Root cause: The ASL setup against GPN # 1027766 has been created on 25th March which has the consigned flag as 'Y'. However, the GPN attribute 'Consigned' at the org level has been set to 'N'.  Here are the screenshots for your reference.

https://screenshot.googleplex.com/C64p3uxxU4C.png

https://screenshot.googleplex.com/1aSs7NCMWxP.png

To fix this, the consigned attribute needs to be set to 'Y' or the consigned flag in ASL setup needs to be unchecked to 'N'.

Thanks,
Aditya+Smita

Summary: Needing DISP Location added in MRB portal for Hard Drives.
Description:
Hello Team,

We are needing WHOKPCPM added as a mapped DISP LOCATION for all Western Digital/ Hitachi HDD's that disposition as RTV-RMA, RTV-PO and MRB. The Box ID shows a To Location as WHOKPCPM, and when you first locate the Box ID in MRB portal, it shows WHOKPCPM as well. When you double click on the line, it changes to blank and only gives a DISP LOCATION of WHOKPCP (MAIN) to choose from the list. WHOKPCPM needs added as DISP LOCATION so that we can send these back to the Vendor. I am attaching a link of the screenshots.

https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1rsA4INTH08yXF_OTQXtJ3Yh1jaZR0zPG?usp=sharing

Thank you,
Robyn Hicks.
Worklog:
Thanks for reaching out to ASCII Oracle Support team for help. This ticket has been triaged by Ticketron, a Google AI powered solution. For more information, please visit go/ticketron.Hi Robyn,

Please let us know if anything required.

Regards,
SurendraHello Team,

This is now corrected in MRB Portal. Your assistance on this issue is greatly appreciated.

Thank you,
Robyn Hicks.Hi Robyn,

Thanks for the confirmation.

Summary: Aging in ODW onhand table
Description:
Hi Team

The Odw_InvDlySnap_F table in PLX has a field average_age_since_original_receipt. I understand this is the average age of the items in the given location. Could you please confirm if this is the weighted average age and how it is calculated?

My understanding is that this field is coming from Oracle and is not a computed field in PLX - hence selected the bizApps-Oracle group

Thanks
Worklog:
Thanks for reaching out to bizApps-Oracle Support team for help. This ticket has been triaged by Ticketron, a Google AI powered  solution. For more information, please visit go/ticketron.Hi ASCII Team,

Could you please look into the request. 
Please help reassign the ticket to concerned team if routed incorrectly. 

Thanks,
Pooja HThanks for reaching out to ASCII Oracle Support team for help. This ticket has been triaged by Ticketron, a Google AI powered solution. For more information, please visit go/ticketron.Hi Aditya, 

Field average_age_since_original_receipt is generated from the query in the below screenshot. 
---------------------------------
select ROUND(SAFE_DIVIDE(SUM(primary_transaction_quantity
              * DATE_DIFF(DATE(CURRENT_TIMESTAMP()),
                         DATE(TIMESTAMP(orig_date_received)),
                         DAY
                        )
              ),
              SUM(primary_transaction_quantity))
         ) AS average_age_since_original_receipt FROM
    OF_Raw.Odw_MtlOnhandQuantitiesDetail_S 
-----------------------------------

https://screenshot.googleplex.com/1tOkHf3uGte

Thanks,
Piyush

Thanks for the update, Piyush.

Hi Gergo

Per below update, the field average_age_since_original_receipt is calculated by rounding the current time stamp and the field original date received in Oracle mtl_onhand_quantities_Detail table.

If you need any more details, please let me know.

Thanks,
AdityaHi my question is whether the quantity received in the location is taken into account for example

if we receive 100 gpns in one location (and assume on consumption) and a receipt of 10 of the same GPN in the same location in 5 days  the simple mean and weighted average would differ (mean: 5+1/6 = 3 days , weighted average age: (5*100 + 10*1)/110  =  4.64 days )
(we can argue whether receipt on the day should be counted as 1 or zero but that's beside the point)

ThanksThanks for the update, Gergo.

I am looking into this. I shall provide you an update at the earliest.

Thanks,
AdityaHi Gergo

The value of the GPN is based on a weighted average of receipt costs over the past number of days, starting with the current date. This calculation excludes any cancelled receipts and then averages all of the receipt costs. Also you can perpetually value inventory at an average cost, weighted by quantity (inventory cost = average unit cost * quantity).

For purchased items, this is a weighted average of the actual procurement cost of an item. For manufactured items, this is a weighted average of the cost of all resources and materials consumed.

Hope this clarifies your query. If you are looking for any additional information, please let me know.

Thanks,
AdityaThanks Adity thats very helpful

Summary: Updating of Oracle Accounting Thresholds
Description:
I would like to have the Oracle control thresholds updated.
Currently per https://b.corp.google.com/issues/30004892 the thresholds are 

     1) Change unit cost beyond a threshold amount (e.g. 1000 USD)
           2) Have an impact on inventory cost beyond a threshold amount (e.g. 25000 USD)

I would like to update the unit cost (note 1) from 1000 USD up to 1500 USD.

there is a bug created for this, but no one is action-ing it. https://buganizer.corp.google.com/issues/124440277
